        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1969-12-15T10:41:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1969-12-15T10:41:00-05:00" n="26"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d26">
                <head>26. Transcript of a Telephone Conversation Between the President’s Assistant
                    for National Security Affairs (<persName corresp="#p_KHA1">Kissinger</persName>)
                    and Secretary of Labor <persName corresp="#p_SGP1">Shultz</persName>
                    <note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d26fn1">Source: National Archives, <persName
                            corresp="#p_NRM1">Nixon</persName> Presidential Materials, <gloss
                            target="#t_NSC1">NSC</gloss> Files, <persName corresp="#p_KHA1"
                            >Kissinger</persName> Telephone Conversation Transcripts, Box 3,
                        Chronological Files. No classification marking.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>Washington</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian"
                            when="1969-12-15T10:41:00-05:00">December 15, 1969, 10:41 a.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <gloss target="#t_S1">S</gloss> said he was calling to see if there had been any
                    word on the oil problem. <gloss target="#t_K1">K</gloss> said he doesn’t see how
                    he can make a national security objection, and that is the only thing I am
                    competent to make. <gloss target="#t_S1">S</gloss> said okay thank you very
                    much. <gloss target="#t_K1">K</gloss> said right; you have your own problem with
                    Defense and the <gloss target="#t_JCS1">JCS</gloss> which I understand you are
                    dealing with. <gloss target="#t_S1">S</gloss> said yes; Defense is on board;
                    they talk like they’re not, but they are. <gloss target="#t_S1">S</gloss> said
                    is it okay for me to say you have no objection on a national security basis?
                        <gloss target="#t_K1">K</gloss> said yes, with Presidential perspective.
                        <gloss target="#t_S1">S</gloss> said okay thank you.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
